### =============================================================================
### Java pipeline head-to-head vs LlamaIndex experiment
###
### PDFs already ingested in document_chunks:
###   - spring-boot-qa       (11 chunks, TextChunker)
###   - jvm-flags-guide      (10 chunks, TextChunker)
###
### LlamaIndex corpus in data_llamaindex_chunks:
###   - same 2 PDFs          (17 chunks, SentenceSplitter, 512 tokens)
###
### Java uses HYBRID by default via RagRetriever.retrieve(docId, question, topK).
### For the head-to-head we compare Java HYBRID vs LlamaIndex HYBRID on the same
### 2 questions that drove findings #4–#6.
###
### For each response, capture into notes.md:
###   - answer                  (LLM output)
###   - chunks[].text           (top-5 retrieved content, first 120 chars is enough)
###   - bestScore               (Java's per-retrieval confidence)
###   - judge.score / grounded  (your internal judge's take — bonus data point)
### =============================================================================

@host = http://localhost:8080


### =============================================================================
### QUESTION 1: Heap sizing (the mixed-corpus question)
###
### LlamaIndex results to beat:
###   Vector  : clean, -Xms1024m -Xmx4096m, top-1 score 0.67
###   BM25    : clean, -Xms512m -Xmx4g,     top-1 @Repository (irrelevant), score 2.83
###   Hybrid  : HALLUCINATED "CPU core's worth of memory" — the failure case
###
### Java hybrid is weighted linear combination of vector + BM25 scores.
### Prediction: Java should NOT hallucinate because the scoped docId prevents
### cross-doc pollution. That's also the key structural difference — Java
### retrieval is doc-scoped by design, LlamaIndex is corpus-wide.
### =============================================================================

### Q1a: Heap sizing, scoped to JVM flags PDF (answer lives here)
POST {{host}}/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "docId": "jvm-flags-guide",
  "question": "How should I configure heap size for a Spring Boot app in production?",
  "topK": 5
}

### Q1b: Heap sizing, scoped to Spring Boot PDF (should return weak/irrelevant chunks)
### This isolates: "what happens when retrieval can't find the real answer?"
POST {{host}}/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "docId": "spring-boot-qa",
  "question": "How should I configure heap size for a Spring Boot app in production?",
  "topK": 5
}


